name: No gaps between adjacent units, max. vertical height prior to backfill is 2 units, min. pin connections per block is 2 upper and 2 lower.
Confirm front face alignment in each course is within the allowable tolerance
Inspect wall batter, wall batter to be within 2 degrees of design batter.
Confirm density results before placing Geogrid layer
Confirm the correct length of Geogrid
Inspect bodkin joints (where used) to join shorter pieces of Geogrid, 1 max. per length of Geogrid.
Confirm the correct elevation of Geogrid.
Ensure Geogrid is placed flat on top of the compacted layer
Ensure Geogrid is connected correctly to the block pin connectors.
Max horizontal distance between geogrids at wall face is 10mm
Ensure plant does not track over Geogrid
Tension geogrid and peg to hold geogrid tight
Place backfill across the geogrid, plant can track onto geogrid when 150mm min backfill has been placed
Monitor plant and equipment keep 1m from front face of wall.
The above works have been inspected and are considered compliant with the drawings, specifications and instructions
(Note: Attach a sketch showing grid on a separate sheet as necessary)
